data: Humza talks about his childhood memories of Ameh. Later, D-Dark requests to stay at Humza’s house, Humza agrees after D-Dark tells him that he would buy his iPhone app. The next day, D-Dark and Humza talk about what they would buy if they were rich. The next day, Humza steals Ameh’s credit card and buys luggage. He then talks about reminiscing over childhood photos with his auntie. The next day, Agent Kalia, Asif and Dexter accuse Humza of bribing a policeman to cavity search them and ask Humza where he is getting all his money from. Dexter defeats Asif in a fight, and later Asif is taken to hospital. The next day, Ameh receives the credit card bill and throws Humza against a shed. Humza talks about advice he received from his father about women. The next day, D-Dark steals Ameh’s purse, pushes Ameh aside and runs out the house. The next day, Agent Kalia, Asif and Dexter force Humza to apologise to Ameh for stealing her credit card. Humza learns that you are not entitled to take something that does not belongs to you but you are entitled to take what God has given you. Humza and Ameh hug and tell each other they love each other. Later, whilst Humza is out buying Ameh flowers, Ameh collapses and dies of a heart-attack from the shock of D-Dark pushing her. Humza returns to find his friends standing besides Ameh lying on her bed, after realising she is dead Humza bursts into tears. Humza remembers Ameh and her memories by a seaside.

Humza talks about Ameh’s funeral and the Olympic Games. Later, he talks about Ramadhan and Asian people’s lack of manners. Humza’s father shouts at his employees and requests one of them, Azmat, to cross-dress and tell him he loves him, who reluctantly agrees. Humza’s father then assaults an unhappy, female customer. Humza talks to Umar about his concern for how his father is dealing with Ameh’s death, and they then kidnap a bride for him. To help distract Humza, his father gets him a job at Dexter’s pizza shop, Super Singh’s Pizza. Humza makes an advert for the pizza shop. Later, Dexter sacks him for writing an insulting message with toppings on a pizza. Meanwhile, D-Dark meets A Squeezy and Klayze with half the money he owes them and admits stealing it from Humza. They force D-Dark to take them to Humza’s house by threatening to harm his hamster. Humza learns that you should appreciate life, not take anything for granted, and aim to better yourself.

Humza arrives home to find his house burgled. Humza talks about having tonsillitis and hospitals. Later, he talks about Eid celebrations. Humza’s father blames him for the burglary and wants him to contribute at least £2,500 by the end of the week or he will burn Humza’s favourite album. Umar calls Humza and tells him that he is pregnant. Humza takes Umar to The Dentist, and bribes The Dentist to convince Umar that he is pregnant. Humza invites his uncle and asks him for £2,500, who agrees but first sings a song about how he came to England. Humza’s uncle then refuses to give Humza the money, and when Humza threatens to call immigration, his uncle runs away. To raise money Humza and Jazzie attempt to rob a butcher’s shop and get chased out by the employees with knives. Jazzie flirts with a girl in Humza’s father’s shop and then argues with her. Humza attempts to rob the girl but gets assaulted and has his phone stolen. Humza meets A Squeezy and Klayze to loan money, he questions where the money came from and Klayze reveals that they burgled Humza’s house. A Squeezy deflects a punch from an angry Humza but after seeing Dexter with a stick, the pair blame D-Dark and run away in fear. A car chase ensues between Agent Kalia and Humza, and D-Dark but D-Dark escapes. Humza learns that if you feel that life is not worth living you should have faith and remember that God does not burden a soul beyond that it cannot bear.

Humza talks about his familys’ lack of Christmas celebrations, the 2012 phenomenon, and his scepticism of conspiracy theories. Meanwhile, Humza’s father tells his employees about their upcoming January sales offers. Azmat dissents and is told to clean the toilets with his face. Kamran requests his wages and gets £5 taken from him. Humza tells Umar he has a girlfriend. Humza’s father finds out, chases him with a rolling pin and headbutts him. His father then advises him on how to court women, talks about his own marriage and tells him that he should let him find him a wife. Humza’s father suggests potential marriage partners for Humza and refuses to let Humza marry his girlfriend. Humza takes his uncle’s advice and runs away. Humza’s father assaults Dexter and orders Asif and Agent Kalia to find Humza in Malaysia. When Asif and Agent Kalia arrive in Malaysia, Humza’s father, whilst holding Asif’s mother captive, calls Asif and tells him he has 24 hours to find Humza or Asif’s mother will be killed. Asif and Agent Kalia find Humza on a beach and chase him. Humza gets bitten by a snake whilst urinating in the bushes and faints. He awakens to find Agent Kalia posing with the snake while Asif takes pictures. Asif attempts to kill the snake with a spade. Humza gets bitten by another snake whilst trying to lure the snake off. They then set the snakes on fire and when Humza asks his friends to suck the venom out, his friends decide to take him to a hospital. Two days later, Humza learns that avoiding a problem makes it worse and the easiest way to escape a problem is to solve it. Also that one should love the people God gave you as one day they will be gone.

When Asif and Agent Kalia arrive in Malaysia, Humza’s father, whilst holding Asif’s mother captive, calls Asif and tells him he has 24 hours to find Humza or Asif’s mother will be killed. Asif and Agent Kalia find Humza on a beach and chase him. Humza gets bitten by a snake whilst urinating in the bushes and faints. He awakens to find Agent Kalia posing with the snake while Asif takes pictures. Asif attempts to kill the snake with a spade. Humza gets bitten by another snake whilst trying to lure the snake off. They then set the snakes on fire and when Humza asks his friends to suck the venom out, his friends decide to take him to a hospital. Two days later, Humza learns that avoiding a problem makes it worse and the easiest way to escape a problem is to solve it. Also that one should love the people God gave you as one day they will be gone.

Humza talks about being ill, Somalis and Asian families behaviour when abroad on holidays. Humza meets Asif, Agent Kalia and Dexter and tells them that he wants to marry his girlfriend of two weeks. Humza gets diarrhea whilst out with his friends. He then visits Smokey’s to get a haircut, after Jazzie throws Agent Kalia out of the barbers for holding his hand, Humza’s sister appears at the barbers. Humza tells Jazzie and his sister that he has a girlfriend, after they laugh at him, he asks for their help. Humza talks about the way “freshies” talk and relationships with parents. Humza is ridiculed by his sister for wearing her bathrobe, who he then pays to help him impress his girlfriend. Humza’s sister advises him to put his girlfriend first, take her to the cinema, take her to a fancy restaurant, take her bowling, and buy her an expensive gift. Humza’s father talks about his first love. Humza takes his girlfriend out and gives her a Lidl bag as a gift. Humza thanks his sister who warns him to be careful or he will get hurt. Humza calls his girlfriend from his father’s shop, who tells him she is shopping. Humza’s father tells Humza that he knows he still has a girlfriend so he will take him to Pakistan. Humza tells his father that he has to accept that he is in love with his girlfriend. Humza’s father tells him that he does not want him to get hurt. Humza leaves the shop ignoring his father’s advice and then sees his girlfriend courting another man. Humza reveals an engagement ring. Humza learns that trying to forget someone you love is like trying to remember someone you never knew. However, God is the reason why even in sadness, we smile; in confusion, we understand; in betrayal, we trust and even in heartbreak... we still love.

data: When a series of murders are committed across London with the same motive, it is suspected that Andrew Dillon, a serial killer from six years previous has returned to commit further crimes. However, Brooks and Devlin manage to track a new man down, and it seems that he was also responsible for the deaths Dillon supposedly committed. However, an alibi provided at the time by a deceased witness seemed to leave Dillon in the clear, despite the fact there is no evidence to back it up either way. It never reached court, however, so it would seem Steel apparently deleted the alibi and is accused of perverting the course of justice. Finding himself on the wrong side of the law, Steel battles for his career and his freedom. Final appearance of James Steel and George Castle

Humza talks about Pakistanis being stereotypically late and then talks about how he usually spends Eid with his uncles and aunties. Two days before Eid, Imam Ali Khan catches Humza looking at obscene pictures on his computer and asks Humza to go to a charity event with him, Humza makes excuses and then refuses to go. However, Ameh forces him to go or he will not receive any money for Eid. Humza reluctantly attends a charity meeting with Umar, Imam Ali Khan and three other men. After Humza and Umar interrupt the meeting, Imam Ali Khan pulls them aside and scolds them. Umar then runs off when one of the other men confronts Humza. On Eid, Humza is stabbed by Ameh after he throws a snowball at her. He then meets Umar and gets invited to a party by a friend of Umar’s, Zebbie, who is accompanied by two girls, Humza agrees to come at the request of one of the girls. Humza is confronted by seven male youths who attack him with snowballs. Humza reveals that attending the charity event made him realise that he can be selfish and made him learn that there are people less fortunate than him, and he donates his Eid money to charity. Humza decides not to go to the party and visits Imam Ali Khan to spend the day together instead.

People all over the world experience bizarre encounters involving strange new creatures in the oceans. Fearing the end of the world, Laura and Rich are determined to find the mysterious corporation that funded this experiment gone awry, but nothing could prepare them for what they discover in an abandoned laboratory along the way. Meanwhile, Miles joins Bloom and his crew of aquarium workers on a boat excursion to find the egg field containing millions of unhatched creatures. Surprisingly, Miles later agrees to help law enforcement find Nim.

With a tsunami approaching the coast, the residents of Wilmington find themselves under a mandatory evacuation. Rich is trapped in the lab after mysteriously finding a picture of the missing Jackson on a computer, but Laura arrives and manages to rescue him. At the same time, Caitlin is knocked out trying to reach Miles and doesn't make it to the ferry in time, so Miles goes after her. He finds her and they race for safety in his parents' car and encounter Laura and Rich on the way. The four head for an open drawbridge, but the car runs out of gas and the tsunami is quickly approaching so they quickly dash into a church and to the roof of the steeple as the tsunami hits and the creatures invade the church. There, the group is reunited with Nimrod and look out upon the completely flooded town, causing Laura to comment that "it is a new world."

data: When prisoner officer Charlie Tyner is found shot dead on a council estate in Hackey, suspicion falls on Ellis Bevan (Ceyln Jones), who was hounded by Tyner is prison for being a child molester. However, it is not long before Brooks & Devlin discover that Tyner was corrupt, and not only was he dealing heroin to the prisoners in his care, he was taking advantage of their situation and raping them as well. Suspicion falls on prisoner Tamika Vincent (Wunmi Mosaku), who became pregnant at the hands of Tyner during one of his sordid sexual adventures. They soon discover that Tyner's drug dealer was Jackson Marshall (Robbie Gee), a career criminal who has evaded the justice system for too long, and that Marshall also has a connection with Tamika - she is serving a sentence for being a mule for Marshall and smuggling drugs into the country for him. With two motives to kill - the fact that Tyner owed him money, and that he raped his mule Tamika - James and Alesha find themselves at odds with George, who is keen to bring justice to the murder of a prison officer. When it is discovered that Tamika ordered Marshall to kill Tyner after her months of abuse, the crown prosecution service believe they finally have the opportunity to bring Marshall to justice.

They soon discover that Tyner's drug dealer was Jackson Marshall (Robbie Gee), a career criminal who has evaded the justice system for too long, and that Marshall also has a connection with Tamika - she is serving a sentence for being a mule for Marshall and smuggling drugs into the country for him. With two motives to kill - the fact that Tyner owed him money, and that he raped his mule Tamika - James and Alesha find themselves at odds with George, who is keen to bring justice to the murder of a prison officer. When it is discovered that Tamika ordered Marshall to kill Tyner after her months of abuse, the crown prosecution service believe they finally have the opportunity to bring Marshall to justice.
